 Huey said she had seen Francis on a practice track at Seoul and he had greeted her as an old friend. "Charlie came over to me and we started talking," Huey said. "We were talking about how Ben might do.
 Charlie said, 'Ben's more afraid of failing the drug test than he is of Carl Lewis.' He was bragging." Huey said she is tired of hearing Francis, who has been in Toronto testifying at a Canadian inquiry into drug use in sport, say that Johnson was clean at the Olympics.
